Given the structures and signature below:

```csharp
    public struct SeqStruct
    {
        public int a;
        public bool b;
        public string str;

        public SeqStruct(int _a, bool _b, string _str)
        {
            a = _a;
            b = _b;
            str = String.Concat(_str, "");
        }
    }

    public struct NestedStruct
    {
        public SeqStruct value;
    }

    [DllImport("LayoutClassNative")]
    private static extern bool SimpleNestedLayoutClassByValue(NestedStruct p);
```

And the native side:

```cpp
struct SeqClass
{
    int a; 
    bool b;
    char* str;
};
struct NestedLayoutClass
{
    SeqClass str;
};

extern "C" DLL_EXPORT BOOL STDMETHODCALLTYPE SimpleNestedLayoutClassByValue(NestedLayoutClass v);
```

The SystemV ABI expects the `v` parameter to be enregistered. However, the runtime passes the value of `v` on the stack instead of enregistering it. I've traced the problem to be
https://github.com/dotnet/coreclr/blob/12a8870119b3e8023d68868792b29c28991168b3/src/vm/methodtable.cpp#L2651-L2656

This check is too broad eagerly marks the `NestedStruct` type as not enregisterable.

This bug is blocking one of the tests in #20867.

