This adds API support for the new C# 8 feature to call dispose asynchronously:

```C#
await using(var stream = File.OpenWrite(path))
{
    await data.WriteAsync(stream);
}
```

For more details, see:

https://github.com/dotnet/csharplang/blob/master/proposals/async-streams.md

Please open new .NetStandard branch with deep refresh of .Net API surface.
Currently .NetStandard 2.0 and it's successor .NetStandard 2.1 contains everything that were added in .net since version 1.0. Some API is already outdated and another will become outdated soon.

.Net Standard 2.1 have some positive movements. It's drops some components to out of standard into additional components.

But it's not enough. It's time to stay in .Net Standard only good and modern parts.
For example:
```CSharp
public class List<T>
{
     // ...
     void CopyTo(T[] array);
     // ...
}
```
can be replaced with:

```CSharp
public class List<T>
{
     // ...
     void CopyTo(Span<T> output);
     // ...
}
```
Assemblies targeting .NetStandard 2.0, .NetStandard 2.1 and proposed .NetStandard 3.0.0 should be capable to work side-by-side inside the same AppDomain.

